  "identifier": "HB 516",
  "title": "AN ACT relating to retirement benefits for probationary employment.",
  "abstract": "Amend KRS 61.552 to allow employees to purchase service credit for the time spent as a probationary employee; amend KRS 78.510 to redefine \"employee,\" \"member\", and \"participating\" to include, solely for the purpose of benefits payable to a person employed in a full-time position or a probationary position, employees who become disabled or die as a direct result of an act in line of duty or as a result of a duty-related injury.",
